President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences to the people of Poland on the tragic deaths of President Lech Kaczynski, First Lady Maria Kaczynski, and others who were traveling with them. The group was on their way to commemorate the 70th anniversary of the Katyn massacre. President Kaczynski was recognized as a distinguished statesman and admired for his dedication to advancing freedom and human dignity. The loss is devastating to Poland, the United States, and the world. The United States values its strong alliance and friendships with Poland, and the strength of the Polish people will help them emerge from this tragedy. The legacy of the leaders who died will continue to guide Poland and the world towards human progress.